Key Match Events: The Wolves committed just one turnover in the first quarter and jumped out to an early 13-point lead.
The Blazers generated energy from their defense and started to unravel the Wolves' momentum in the second quarter.
Portland scored 21 points off of the Wolves' 14 turnovers, while Minnesota scored only 12 points off Portland's 20 turnovers.
Post-Match Reflections: Head Coach Chris Finch mentioned the team's struggles and noted it's early in the season.
Finch emphasized that the team needs to improve their three-point shooting and overall execution.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Donte DiVincenzo struggled with his performance, shooting 1-10 from the field and 0-6 from three-point range.
Rob Dillingham showed promise in his first meaningful regular season minutes, playing well defensively and showing a pass-first mindset.
